RockYou — Licensing
===================

This repository is split-licensed on purpose. Two goals pull in different
directions, so two licenses apply:

  1. The reverse-engineered Roku ECP-2 protocol layer is the part worth
     sharing with the world — the hard-won knowledge about the undocumented
     authenticated WebSocket protocol Roku devices actually speak, plus the
     discovery and parsing code around it. Improvements to it should flow
     back. It is licensed under the Mozilla Public License 2.0 (file-level
     copyleft): use it, ship it inside anything you like, but if you change
     one of those files, publish your changes to that file.

  2. Everything else — the application: the UI, the household sync design,
     the watch app, the shader playgrounds, the product design — is
     source-available, not open source. You may read it, run it, learn from
     it, and build non-competing things on it. You may NOT repackage it as a
     competing or substitute product (a rename, a port to another
     language/platform, or a reskin still counts). It is licensed under the
     PolyForm Perimeter License 1.0.1.

Neither is legal advice; both are standard, lawyer-drafted licenses used as-is.

